# Karmalka, Republic of Bashkortostan

}}
Karmalka (; , QaramalÄ±) is a rural locality (a village) in Verkhnetroitsky Selsoviet, Tuymazinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 7 as of 2010. There is 1 street.
Geography
Karmalka is located 38 km south of Tuymazy (the district's administrative centre) by road. Verkhnetroitskoye is the nearest rural locality.
